<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC4FFE8A1987DA195E80B27" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC4FFE8A1987DA195E80B27" blockId="13.[145,761,1786,1900]" lastBlockId="13.[809,1425,197,342]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC4FFE8A1987DA191720D61" box="[145,274,1787,1808]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium adult-sized 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A32D7DA092980D61" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[548,760,1786,1808]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ommastrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Ommastrephidae</taxonomicName>
without photophores; funnel groove without foveola or lateral pockets; tentacles without carpal locking apparatus; tentacle club with manus horny sucker rings smooth or with rounded teeth; eight series of suckers on dactylus; lateral suckers of the paralarva proboscis equal in diameter to the central ones; paralarvae without skin sculpture; adult female without seminal receptacles in the buccal membrane.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
